
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gpu-manager` baraye modiriyat va kontrol kart grafiki (GPU) dar sistem-haye Linux estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta driver-haye sahih ra nasb konid va behtarin performanro az GPU begirid, be khosos baraye bazi-ha va barname-haye sangin.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gpu-manager --list-devices` --> 🔍 List kardan hame device-haye GPU dar system.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --install-driver <driver-name>` --> ⚙️ Nasb kardan yek driver moshakhas baraye GPU.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --uninstall-driver` --> 🗑️ Hazf kardan driver-haye nasb shode GPU.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --check-status` --> ✅ Check kardan vaziat (status) GPU va driver-haye nasb shode.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gpu-manager --list-devices

    🔹 List hameye device-haye GPU.

    $ gpu-manager --install-driver nvidia-driver-535

    🔹 Nasb driver Nvidia ba version 535.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gpu-manager --check-status

    🔹 Check mikonad ke driver GPU dorost nasb shode va GPU be dorosti kar mikonad ya na. Agar problem bashe, peyghami neshun mide.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gpu-manager` command is used to manage and control graphics cards (GPUs) on Linux systems. It helps you install the correct drivers and optimize GPU performance, especially for gaming and resource-intensive applications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gpu-manager --list-devices` --> 🔍 List all GPU devices in the system.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --install-driver <driver-name>` --> ⚙️ Install a specific driver for the GPU.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --uninstall-driver` --> 🗑️ Uninstall the currently installed GPU driver.
    🔹 `gpu-manager --check-status` --> ✅ Check the status of the GPU and installed drivers.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gpu-manager --list-devices

    🔹 Lists all GPU devices.

    $ gpu-manager --install-driver nvidia-driver-535

    🔹 Installs the Nvidia driver version 535.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gpu-manager --check-status

    🔹 Checks if the GPU driver is correctly installed and if the GPU is working properly. If there's a problem, it displays a message.
